================================================================================
VS Code shell-integration scripts
================================================================================

The following files under `resources/shell-integration/` are vendored verbatim
from microsoft/vscode at tag v1.95.3 (path:
src/vs/workbench/contrib/terminal/common/scripts/):

  - shellIntegration-bash.sh
  - shellIntegration-env.zsh
  - shellIntegration-login.zsh
  - shellIntegration-profile.zsh
  - shellIntegration-rc.zsh
  - shellIntegration.fish        (from fish_xdg_data/fish/vendor_conf.d/)
  - shellIntegration.ps1

These files are used at runtime to enable OSC 633 shell-integration markers
inside AnyWhere Terminal sessions, mirroring the behavior of VS Code's
integrated terminal.

